{"title":"ImportError overview","date":"2019-12-28T09:27:25.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Dec 28, 2019","L":"12/28/2019","MM-DD":"12-28"},"link":"2019/12/28/ImportError-overview","tags":["Tensorflow"],"updated":"2020-03-21T19:30:09.862Z","content":"<p>This article aim to deal with some errors, which occurs in the process of you import some package of tensorflow.</p>\n\n\n<h1 id=\"ImportError-cannot-import-name-‘tf-utils’\">ImportError: cannot import name ‘tf_utils’<a href=\"2019/12/28/ImportError-overview#ImportError-cannot-import-name-‘tf-utils’\"></a></h1><p>Seems like it was a problem with keras 2.3.0, I installed keras 2.1.5 using pip and it works fine.</p>\n<p>pip install keras==2.1.5</p>\n<h1 id=\"No-module-named-‘colors’\">No module named ‘colors’<a href=\"2019/12/28/ImportError-overview#No-module-named-‘colors’\"></a></h1><p>pip install colors.py</p>\n","prev":{"title":"hexo+GitHub pages deploy","link":"2020/01/14/hexo+github pages deploy"},"next":{"title":"Ubuntu: Software source","link":"2019/12/28/Software source of Ubuntu"},"plink":"https://thswind.github.io/2019/12/28/ImportError-overview/","toc":[{"title":"ImportError: cannot import name ‘tf_utils’","id":"ImportError-cannot-import-name-‘tf-utils’","index":"1"},{"title":"No module named ‘colors’","id":"No-module-named-‘colors’","index":"2"}],"reward":true,"copyright":{"custom":"禁止转载-非商用-THSWind"}}